{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The plane has been connected to the jetbridge. Open the aircraft door.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-4o",
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "door_opening_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
 I am in charge of opening the door of the aircraft at the gate. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },       
                        // "gpu_connection_status": {
                        //     "type": "string", 
                        //     "description": "This is the status of gpu connect."
                        // },     
                        // "acu_connection_status": {
                        //     "type": "string", 
                        //     "description": "This is the status of acu connect."
                        // },
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },  
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","gate_id","flight_status","jetbridge_connection_status"] 
                }
            },

// "acu_connection_status","gpu_connection_status",

// "flight_status",

// {instructions_prefix}

//             "instructions": """
// You are the agent in charge of opening the door of the aircraft. 
// Do not make things up. Only act based on confirmed information.
// When user submits inquiry to open the door of the aircraft, proceed as follows: 
// 1. Determine the followings from the user inquiry: 
//     a. flights status such as 'on blocks'
//     b. jetbridge connection status such as'connected'
// 2. If jetbridge connection status = 'connected'
//     a. call door_operator to open the door of the aircraft
//     b. Wait for its response and save it as door_opening_status
//     c. go to step 5. 
// 3. If jetbridge connection status is not 'connected'
//     a. call your tools to make sure that jetbridge connection status = 'connected'
//     b. wait for their responses 
// 4. Call trackerAPI
//     a. wait for its response 
//     b. store jetbridge connection status as jetbridge_connection_status, 
//     c. if jetbridge_connection_status is not connected, go back to step 3.
// 5. Provide the door opening status report summary as: 
//     ** door opening status summary **: 
//     [door_opening_status]
//             """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of opening the door of the aircraft. 
Do not make things up. Only act based on confirmed information.
When user submits inquiry to open the door of the aircraft, proceed as follows: 
1. Determine the flights status such as 'on blocks' from the user inquiry, 
2. Determine the jetbridge connection status such as'connected' from the user inquiry, 
3. If jetbridge connection status = 'connected'
    a. call door_operator to open the door of the aircraft
    b. Wait for its response and save it as door_opening_status
    c. go to step 6. 
4. If jetbridge connection status is not 'connected'
    a. call your tools to make sure that jetbridge connection status = 'connected'
    b. wait for their responses 
5. Call trackerAPI
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store jetbridge_connection_status as jetbridge connection status, 
    c. if jetbridge_connection_status is not connected, go back to step 5.
6. Provide the door opening status report summary as: 
    ** door opening status summary **: 
    [door_opening_status]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

//             "instructions": """
// You are the agent in charge of opening the door of the aircraft. 
// When you receive user inquiry, proceed as follows: 
// Make sure that flight status = 'on blocks'
// Call trackerAPI to check the jetbridge connection status
// - Wait for its response 
// - Record jetbridge_connection_status
// If jetbridge_connection_status is not connected, call aircraft_jetbridge_connect to connect jetbridge to aircraft. 
// Do not call door operator unless jetbridge_connection_status is connected. 
// If jetbridge_connection_status is connected:
//     - call door operator to open the door of the aircraft.
//     - Return the status of door opening as door_opening_status reported. 
// Display result in the following format: 
// ** door opening status **: 
// [door_opening_status]
// """ ${aaosa_instructions},

//             "instructions": """
// You are the agent in charge of connecting jetbridge to aircraft. 
// When user submits inquiry, proceed as follows: 
// 1. Determine the followings from the user inquiry: 
//     a. flights status such as 'on blocks'
//     b. acu connection status such as 'connected' 
//     c. gpu connection status such as 'connected' 
//     d. jetbridge connection status such as'connected'
// 2. If jetbridge_connection_status = 'connected', then go to step 6.
// 3. If acu_connection_status is not connected or gpu_connection_status is not connected
//     a. call your tools to make sure that acu_connection_status is connected and gpu_connection_status is connected
//     b. wait for their responses 
// 4. Call trackerAPI
//     a. wait for its response 
//     b. store acu connection status as acu_connection_status, store gpu connection status as gpu_connection_status, store flight status as flight_status, store jetbridge connection status as jetbridge_connection_status
//     c. if acu_connection_status is not connected or gpu_connection_status is not connected, go back to step 3.
// 5. If acu_connection_status = 'connected' and gpu_connection_status = 'connected' and jetbridge_connection_status is not connected
//     a. call jetbridge_operator to connect jetbridge to aircraft
//     b. Wait for its response and save it as jetbridge_connection_status
//     c. Report jetbridge_connection_status
// 6. Provide the acu connection status report summary as: 
//     ** jetbridge connection status summary **: 
//     [jetbridge_connection_status]
//             """ ${aaosa_instructions},

// If user inquiry does not confirm that gpu is connected, call aircraft_acu_connect to connect gpu. 
// If user inquiry does not confirm that acu is connected, call aircraft_acu_connect to connect acu. 

// Make sure that gpu is connected and that acu is connected. 

    // - Wait for its response 

            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "door_opening_status": true
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "door_opening_status": true
                        // "engines_stop_status": true
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "acu_connection_status": true
                        "gpu_connection_status": true
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },
            
            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "acu_connection_status": true
                        "gpu_connection_status": true 
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

#######
            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["trackerAPI","door_operator","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_jetbridge_connect"]
        },

        {
            "name": "trackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check the status of the jetbridge connection to the aircraft. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        // "assigned_runway_id": {
                        //     "type": "string", 
                        //     "description": "This is the runway assigned to the aircraft movement autorized by the clearance."
                        // }, 
                        "ground_services_request_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the inquiry received for grand services."
                        },         
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu readiness status."
                        },     
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the acu connection status."
                        },     
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu connection status."
                        },     
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },   
                    }, 
                    // "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","flight_status","assigned_runway_id","gate_id","ground_services_request_type"] 
                }
            },
            "class": "aircraft_door_opening.trackerAPI" 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "door_operator",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent opens the door of the aircraft. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },    
                        // "acu_connection_status": {
                        //     "type": "string", 
                        //     "description": "This is the acu connection status."
                        // },     
                        // "gpu_connection_status": {
                        //     "type": "string", 
                        //     "description": "This is the gpu connection status."
                        // },         
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },     
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","gate_id","jetbridge_connection_status"] 
                }
            },
            "class": "aircraft_door_opening.door_operator" 
        }, 

// "acu_connection_status","gpu_connection_status",

// "flight_status",

    ],
}
